# Additional files stripped from the WordPress.org build, on top of .zipignore.
#
# Everything listed here is commercial-distribution-only logic. The theme must
# keep working without these files: functions.php and inc/admin/admin.php load
# them through file_exists() guards.

# The commercial distribution loader and the code it pulls in (WUpdates
# self-updates, CDN webfonts fallback, remote vendor scripts).
inc/distribution.php
inc/distribution

# NOTE: The Pixelgrade Assistant install notice (inc/admin/assistant-notice/)
# and its theme-support integration (inc/integrations/pixelgrade-assistant.php)
# are intentionally NOT stripped — they ship in the WordPress.org build too. The
# plugin install/activate is driven entirely by WordPress core (wp.updates) and
# targets the wp.org-hosted `pixelgrade-assistant` slug, so they are bare-build
# safe and Theme-Check clean.

# The wp.org overlay source folder itself (its contents are copied into the
# build root by the build:wporg:overlay task).
